
# Git :: Conventional commits
#
#  - The HEADER is mandatory, scope is optional, subject is mandatory
#      + <type>    Kind of change this commit is providing
#                      * build (affect build system or external dependency)
#                      * chore (maintenance change)
#                      * ci (change to CI configuration file / script)
#                      * docs (documentation)
#                      * feat (new feature)
#                      * fix (bug fix)
#                      * function (improving functionality)
#                      * perf (improving performance)
#                      * refactor (change neither fixes bug nor adds a feature)
#                      * style (white-space, formatting, missing semicolons, ...)
#                      * test (correcting or missing test)
#      + <scope>   Anything specifying the place of the commit change
#      + <subject> Very short description of the change
#                      * imperative, present tense: 'change' not 'changed'/'changes'
#                      * no capitalised first letter
#                      * no dot (.) at the end
#
#  - The BODY should include the motivation for the change in imperative present tense
#  - The FOOTER should contain information about Breaking changes and/or references to issue #
#
#  - The message FORMAT
#      <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#      <BLANK LINE>
#      <body>
#      <BLANK LINE>
#      <footer>
#
